                   Back to home !!<br>
<br>
Altough there is no night nor day in my home city, it was an hour people prefer to stay at home. In fact, it was one of the hours the city no longer belong to the commun citizens, but to the ebony hand looking to complete his contract and to the hungry ghoul in quest of a lost soul nobody will regret.<br>
<br>
Any commun citizen would have closed his homedoor and prefered a dream world to the horrors who haunt Neriak during these hours. But i am no longer a commun citizen and i don't have anymore a place i can call 'home'.<br>
<br>
I hardly remembered my way through that labyrinthe of dark streets. I quitted my native town so much time ago i was feeling a stranger. Altough i changed during my adventures in the outside world, the city didn't. I was still smelling fear, hate and peasure like in my childhood. The old feelings were bringing back a lot of old memories and i closed for a few seconds my eyes and smiled to that old time. <br>
<br>
Closing your eyes in an assassin's city ? Some people would answer i was a fool. But i think the fool was that hidden smuggler who was using the shadows to spot me. He jumped out of the dark, a poor quality dagger in the right hand.<br>
<br>
I didn't even turned to face him. I just walked slowly ahead, hoping his screams of pain will be a sufficient warning to the real fools as my loyal air spirit was becoming solid and dismembering him.<br>
<br>
<br>
I finally hit my goal. A large house in the noble section, with a name scribed above the door - a name i have abandonned a long time ago, but a name i didn't forgotten.<br>
<br>
I dismissed the winds and conjured a rock golem, then i surrounded myself and my pet of a fire aura. It was finally the time i waited so much time. Then i striked.<br>
<br>
<br>
The main doors were smashed with a loud crash by my golem. I entered the hall i fleed so many years ago. And i waited.<br>
<br>
Guards arrived a few seconds after. They weren't my goal. A rain of fire fall on them. The survivor died just after, reduced to a pulp of flesh by my shock of sword.<br>
<br>
Then i saw them.. my father, my mother, and my two brothers. They were standing in the stairs, wielding their so precious magic weapons, relics of the combine empire. <br>
<br>
I think i couldn't well scribe down what occured at this time. At this moment i feared my hate would have disappeard. But in the second i knew it wasn't.<br>
<br>
My mother died, reduced to a burning body by my fire.<br>
<br>
My first brother died, as my rock golem smashed his head against the wall.<br>
<br>
My oldest brother died, as he tried to attack me and ignited immediatly because of my fire aura. I let him running around for a few seconds, smiling of pleasure as i feel his immense fear and despair. Then i snaped fingers to order my golem to seal his fate.<br>
<br>
Then i turned to my father.<br>
<br>
'You teached me very well father, in the Ways of Innoruuk. It is now the time for the student to show his progress to his teacher.', i said coldly to him. 'Now i understand you weren't really a follower... you just teached me because of the city's Laws. I will now show you what Your Failure Child can do'<br>
<br>
'It seems to me than my failure child is just gone crazy because of that so-called power of hate!' <br>
<br>
'Perhaps, but right now, it feed me and give me strength.'<br>
<br>
'And because of the Hate, you are killing your own family ?'<br>
<br>
'Right now, it has nothing to do with hate.. it is only pleasure.'<br>
<br>
Nobody in the city moved nor came to see what happened. Although his screams lasted for about one hour. Wisdom is a lesson childrens learn very young in Neriak...<br>
<br>
At the end, i saw a servant hidden in a corner. I walked by her to speak.<br>
<br>
'Stand up Slave. Clean the room and throw the bodies to the ghouls. And then warn the others you have a new Mistress from now.'<br>
<br>
I was finally back home...<br>
<br>
From the notes of Deidril,<br>
Dark elf ,elementalist of Innoruuk (53)<br>
